This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the use of correlation filters for object tracking and detection. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a novel approach to correlation filter estimation. Additionally, it may be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories as it discusses the performance of object tracking and detection algorithms.
